<div id="review_3803623223" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3803623223" />
    <a title="Bidasari" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/108313722-bidasari"><img alt="Bidasari" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1609546112p2/108313722.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3803623223?book_show_action=true">Jan 28, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bidasari" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bidasari" href="/user/show/108313722-bidasari">Bidasari</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer3803623223&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3803623223" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11443675593973642091">Five short stories with the colourful Bombay in the background. <br/><br/>1. Dharma - a war hero with amputated leg must confront the ghost from his past that resides in his house so that both of them can find peace within and move on. <br/><br/>2. Shakti - a woman who knows how to manipulate situations and people to get what she wanted in life in the most subtle way while wearing her sweetest smile. Its like reading one of the strategy in The Arts of War by Tsu Szu being implemented very accurately here. <br/><br/>3. Kama -</span>
  <span id="freeText11443675593973642091" style="display:none">Five short stories with the colourful Bombay in the background. <br /><br />1. Dharma - a war hero with amputated leg must confront the ghost from his past that resides in his house so that both of them can find peace within and move on. <br /><br />2. Shakti - a woman who knows how to manipulate situations and people to get what she wanted in life in the most subtle way while wearing her sweetest smile. Its like reading one of the strategy in The Arts of War by Tsu Szu being implemented very accurately here. <br /><br />3. Kama - an inspector investigating a mysterious murder case while at the same time trying to accept the fact that he will have to let go of his wife no matter how much he loves her. The scene when they were together for the last time is so heartbreaking because you realized that when its time to say goodbye, there is nothing you can do and say because the feeling is too overwhelming. <br /><br />4. Artha - Iqbal experienced the saddest goodbye in his life when Rajesh suddenly dissapeared from his life without explaination and any last word in the cruel world of mobster. <br /><br />5. Shanti - the beauty of friendship between Shiv and Frankie. The support they give each other no matter how absurd the situations they encounter. A very sweet love story when you least expected it. <br /><br />The elaboration on each scene is so rich and vivid that you will feel like you are in Bombay dancing in the some seedy bar, waiting impatiently at the platform for the train to arrive, trying to release yourself from the gangster' grips, telling your side of the story to the police in the rundown police station, running on the streets when there is a clash between the Muslim and Hindu, etc.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11443675593973642091" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


